WEBVTT

00:44.045 --> 00:46.630
<i>[Birds Chirping]</i>

01:11.989 --> 01:14.784
I still don't know
why <i>I'm</i> here.

01:14.867 --> 01:16.827
Couldn't you just
make them say yes?

01:16.911 --> 01:19.205
Yes, I could,
but it's not my way.

01:19.288 --> 01:21.207
And I would expect you,
of all people,

01:21.290 --> 01:24.210
would understand my feelings
about the misuse of power.

01:24.293 --> 01:28.255
Ah, "power corrupts"
and all that.
Yes, I know, Charles.

01:28.339 --> 01:31.217
When are you going to
stop lecturing me?
When you start listening.

01:31.300 --> 01:34.428
[ Chuckles]
And you're here
because I need you.

01:34.512 --> 01:37.431
We're not gonna have to meet
every one of them in person,
are we?

01:37.515 --> 01:41.185
No. This one's special.

01:41.268 --> 01:43.813
What a beautiful campus.

01:43.896 --> 01:46.941
John, don't you think?
Yes, the brochure is great.

01:47.024 --> 01:52.029
But what about Jean?
What about her... illness?

01:52.113 --> 01:54.490
- Illness?
- John.

01:54.573 --> 01:56.826
You think your daughter
is sick, Mr. Grey?

01:56.909 --> 02:00.746
Perhaps it would be best if
we were to speak to her, alone.

02:00.830 --> 02:03.999
Of course.
Jean?

02:04.083 --> 02:06.210
Can you come down, dear?

02:17.012 --> 02:19.640
<i>We'll, uh, leave you then.</i>

02:27.231 --> 02:31.152
<i>[Xavier Thinking]
It's very rude, you know, to read my
thoughts or Mr. Lehnsherr's...</i>

02:31.235 --> 02:33.070
<i>without our permission.</i>

02:33.154 --> 02:36.782
Did you think
you were the only one
of your kind, young lady?

02:36.866 --> 02:40.202
We're mutants, Jean.
We are like you.

02:41.245 --> 02:44.415
Really?
I doubt that.

03:00.639 --> 03:03.017
<i>Oh, Charles.</i>

03:03.100 --> 03:05.227
I like this one.

03:05.311 --> 03:08.856
You have more power
than you can imagine, Jean.

03:08.939 --> 03:12.484
<i>The question is,
will you control that power...</i>

03:15.446 --> 03:17.656
or let it control you?

03:25.873 --> 03:29.126
[ Scraping ]
[ Grunting ]

03:37.718 --> 03:43.098
<i>- Warren? Son, is everything all right?
- [Grunting Continues]</i>

03:43.182 --> 03:46.143
- What's going on in there?
- Nothing! I'll be right out.

03:46.227 --> 03:51.440
Come on. You've been
in there for over an hour.
Open the door.

03:51.523 --> 03:54.026
<i>Warren?</i>
One second!

03:56.362 --> 03:58.572
<i>[Clanking]</i>
Open this door!

03:58.656 --> 04:00.491
- [ Panting ]
<i>- Warren?</i>

04:02.409 --> 04:04.954
<i>Let me in there right now!
Open the door!</i>

04:16.382 --> 04:18.676
[ Sobbing ]

04:20.511 --> 04:22.680
<i>Oh, God.</i>

04:22.763 --> 04:24.723
Not you.

04:24.807 --> 04:27.017
<i>Dad, I'm sorry.</i>

05:54.104 --> 05:57.900
The whole world's goin' to hell,
you're just gonna sit there? Let's go.

06:09.078 --> 06:11.163
<i>[Missile Incoming]</i>
Bobby!

06:17.044 --> 06:19.254
Thanks, Kitty.

06:25.469 --> 06:29.098
- We're getting killed out here.
- Yeah, I know. They're not ready, Storm.

06:29.181 --> 06:31.100
<i>[Rumbling]</i>

06:31.183 --> 06:33.352
<i>- Logan.</i>
- Oh, don't get your panties in a bunch.

06:36.897 --> 06:41.110
[ Panting ]
That was my last cigar.

06:41.193 --> 06:43.946
Logan!

06:44.029 --> 06:46.448
<i>- [Rogue]
It's getting closer!</i>
- [ Rumbling ]

06:46.532 --> 06:51.203
- Come on! Let's keep moving!
- Hey, Tin Man! Come here!

06:51.286 --> 06:54.540
- How's your throwing arm?
- Logan, we work as a team.

06:54.623 --> 06:58.168
Yeah, good luck with that.
Throw me. Now!

06:58.252 --> 07:00.337
<i>[Storm]
Damn it, Logan!
Don't do this!</i>

07:00.421 --> 07:02.965
[ Shouting ]

07:03.048 --> 07:05.300
<i>[Slicing]</i>

07:17.438 --> 07:19.857
Class dismissed.

07:23.944 --> 07:26.864
Hey, Colossus,
nice throw.

07:29.199 --> 07:31.702
<i>[Female Computer Voice]
Simulation complete.</i>

07:35.414 --> 07:37.332
What the hell was that?

07:37.416 --> 07:39.334
Danger Room session.
You know what I mean.

07:39.418 --> 07:42.379
Oh, lighten up, Storm.
Look, you can't just change
the rules when you feel like it.

07:42.463 --> 07:44.840
I'm tryin' to
teach 'em something.
I taught 'em something.

07:44.923 --> 07:49.011
It was a defensive exercise.
Yeah. Best defense
is a good offense.

07:49.094 --> 07:51.930
Or is it
the other way around?
This isn't a game, Logan.

07:52.014 --> 07:54.766
Well, you sure fooled me.

07:54.850 --> 07:58.228
Hey, I'm just a sub.
You got a problem,
talk to Scott.

08:16.121 --> 08:18.665
- Scott!
- Jean.

08:18.749 --> 08:20.959
<i>[Jean's Voice]
Scott. Scott.</i>

08:21.043 --> 08:25.464
<i>Scott. Scott.</i>

08:25.547 --> 08:27.591
<i>[Bobby]
Are you okay?
[Rogue] I'm fine.</i>

08:30.302 --> 08:32.429
Well, you don't seem fine.
You seem like you're
avoiding me.

08:32.513 --> 08:35.724
I mean, something's wrong.
What's wrong is I can't touch
my boyfriend without killin' him.

08:35.807 --> 08:38.059
Other than that,
I'm wonderful.
Hey.

08:38.143 --> 08:41.063
I don't think that's fair.
Have I ever put
any pressure on you?

08:41.145 --> 08:44.441
You're a guy, Bobby.
Your mind's only on one thing.

08:48.153 --> 08:50.822
Hey, Scott,
they were lookin' for you
downstairs. You didn't show.

08:50.906 --> 08:53.825
What do you care?
Well, for starters,
I had to cover your ass.

08:53.909 --> 08:56.203
I didn't ask you to.
No, you didn't.

08:56.286 --> 08:58.997
The professor did.
I was just passing through.

08:59.081 --> 09:02.334
So pass through, Logan.
Hey, look.

09:04.294 --> 09:05.796
I know how you feel.
Don't.

09:05.879 --> 09:08.257
When Jean died‒
I said don't.

09:10.300 --> 09:12.302
Maybe it's time for us
to move on.

09:16.348 --> 09:18.809
Not everybody heals
as fast as you, Logan.

09:42.040 --> 09:44.501
Mr. Secretary?
Yes.

09:46.086 --> 09:48.839
- The meeting's begun, sir.
- Thank you.

09:55.345 --> 09:58.599
Mr. President.
Have a seat, Hank.

10:00.851 --> 10:03.812
Homeland Security
was tracking Magneto.

10:03.895 --> 10:07.566
We got hits in Lisbon,
Geneva, Montreal.

10:07.649 --> 10:09.568
NAVSAT lost him
crossing the border.

10:09.651 --> 10:12.863
But we did get
a consolation prize.

10:12.946 --> 10:15.657
We picked her up
breaking into the F.D.A.,
of all places.

10:15.741 --> 10:19.119
Do you know who
she's been imitating?
Secretary Trask here.

10:19.202 --> 10:22.122
Yes, sir.
She can do that.

10:22.205 --> 10:24.958
Not anymore, she can't.
We got her.

10:25.042 --> 10:27.919
You think your prisons
can hold her?
<i>We have some new prisons, Hank.</i>

10:28.003 --> 10:30.339
We'll keep them mobile.
Be a step ahead this time.

10:30.422 --> 10:33.342
<i>[Man On Speaker]
Where is Magneto?</i>

10:33.425 --> 10:35.344
Raven?

10:35.427 --> 10:38.013
Raven, I asked you a question.

10:38.096 --> 10:40.098
I don't answer
to my slave name.

10:40.182 --> 10:43.268
Raven Darkholme.
That's your real name,
isn't it?

10:43.352 --> 10:46.897
Or has he convinced you
you don't have
a family anymore?

10:46.980 --> 10:50.108
My family tried to kill me,
you pathetic meat sack.

10:51.568 --> 10:53.528
Okay, then. Mystique.

10:53.612 --> 10:55.906
Where is he?

10:58.867 --> 11:00.827
In here with us.

11:00.911 --> 11:04.665
I don't want to
play games with you.
I want answers.

11:04.748 --> 11:06.583
You don't want to
play games with me?

11:06.667 --> 11:10.921
You are gonna stop this.
Tell me, where is Magneto?

11:12.589 --> 11:15.258
You want to know
where he is?

11:23.600 --> 11:25.602
Homo sapien!

11:25.686 --> 11:28.105
[ Gagging ]

11:31.775 --> 11:34.361
You know her capture
will only provoke Magneto.

11:34.444 --> 11:37.406
But having her does give us
some diplomatic leverage.

11:37.489 --> 11:41.368
On principle,
I can't negotiate
with these people.

11:41.451 --> 11:43.745
I thought that's why
you appointed me, sir.

11:43.829 --> 11:45.747
Yes, it is.

11:45.831 --> 11:48.208
But that's not why
you called me here.
No.

11:48.291 --> 11:52.045
This is.
It's what she stole
from the F.D.A.

11:58.510 --> 12:01.888
Dear Lord.

12:01.972 --> 12:05.058
Is it viable?
We believe it is.

12:07.144 --> 12:10.689
You realize the level
of impact this will have
on the mutant community?

12:10.772 --> 12:16.695
Yes, I do.
That's precisely why we need
some of your... diplomacy now.

12:20.407 --> 12:23.243
<i>[Xavier]
When an individual
acquires great power,</i>

12:23.326 --> 12:27.205
the use or misuse of
that power is everything.

12:27.289 --> 12:29.207
Will it be for the greater good?

12:29.291 --> 12:33.920
Or will it be used for personal
or for destructive ends?

12:34.004 --> 12:36.757
Now, this is a question
we must all ask ourselves.

12:36.840 --> 12:39.634
Why?
Because we are mutants.

12:39.718 --> 12:42.554
For psychics, this presents
a particular problem.

12:42.637 --> 12:47.058
<i>When is it acceptable to
use our power, and when do
we cross that in visible line...</i>

12:47.142 --> 12:49.936
<i>that turns us into tyrants
over our fellow man?</i>

12:50.020 --> 12:53.774
But Einstein said that ethics are
an exclusive human concern...

12:53.857 --> 12:56.401
without any superhuman
authority behind it.

12:56.485 --> 13:00.113
Einstein wasn't a mutant...
so far as we know.

13:00.197 --> 13:02.365
[All Chuckling ]

13:02.449 --> 13:07.287
Now, this case study was
sent to me by a colleague,
Dr. Moira MacTaggert. Jones?

13:07.370 --> 13:11.291
The man you see here was born
with no higher-level brain functions.

13:11.374 --> 13:16.171
His organs and nervous system
work, but he has no
consciousness to speak of.

13:16.254 --> 13:19.966
Now, what if we were to transfer
the consciousness of one person,

13:20.050 --> 13:25.806
say a father of four
with terminal cancer,
into the body of this man?

13:25.889 --> 13:30.769
<i>How are we to decide
what falls within the range of
ethical behavior and what‒</i>

13:44.157 --> 13:46.159
Professor?

13:47.744 --> 13:49.788
We'll continue this tomorrow.

13:49.871 --> 13:52.082
Class dismissed.

13:53.959 --> 13:57.212
<i>[ Wind Whistling]</i>

13:59.589 --> 14:02.217
<i>[Xavier]
The forecast was
for sunny skies.</i>

14:02.300 --> 14:05.637
Oh. I'm sorry.

14:14.855 --> 14:18.650
I don't have to be psychic
to see that something's
bothering you.

14:19.818 --> 14:21.736
<i>[Storm]
I don't understand.</i>

14:21.820 --> 14:25.866
<i>Magneto's a fugitive.
We have a mutant in the cabinet,
a president who understands us.</i>

14:25.949 --> 14:29.870
Why are we still hiding?
We're not hiding. But we
still have enemies out there.

14:29.953 --> 14:32.038
And I must
protect my students.
You know that.

14:32.122 --> 14:34.291
Yes, but we can't
be students forever.

14:34.374 --> 14:38.295
[ Chuckles ]
Storm, I hadn't thought of you
as my student for years.

14:38.378 --> 14:43.717
In fact, I thought that,
perhaps, you might
take my place some day.

14:47.220 --> 14:52.934
But Scott's‒
Scott's a changed man.
He took Jean's death so hard.

14:53.018 --> 14:55.228
Yes, things are
better out there.

14:55.312 --> 14:59.065
But you,
of all people, know how fast
the weather can change.

14:59.149 --> 15:01.151
There's something
you're not tellin' us.

15:11.995 --> 15:14.039
<i>[Storm]
Hank?</i>

15:14.122 --> 15:17.083
Ororo! Charles.
[ Chuckles ]

15:17.167 --> 15:19.586
<i>Oh!
[Laughing]</i>

15:19.669 --> 15:22.422
I love what you've done
with your hair.
Mmm. You too.

15:22.505 --> 15:25.717
Thanks.
Thank you for seeing me
on such short notice.

15:25.800 --> 15:29.638
Henry, you are
always welcome here.
You're a part of this place.

15:29.721 --> 15:32.307
- I have news.
- Is it Eric?

15:32.390 --> 15:34.976
No. Though we have been making
some progress on that front.

15:35.060 --> 15:38.355
- Mystique was
recently apprehended.
- Who's the furball?

15:39.439 --> 15:42.233
Hank McCoy,
Secretary of Mutant Affairs.

15:42.317 --> 15:45.028
Right, right.
The secretary.
Nice suit.

15:45.111 --> 15:47.572
- Henry, this is Logan. He's, uh‒
- Wolverine.

15:47.656 --> 15:50.617
- I hear you're quite an animal.
- Look who's talkin'.

15:50.700 --> 15:53.536
<i>You know Magneto's gonna
come get Mystique, right?</i>

15:53.620 --> 15:57.457
Magneto's not the problem.
At least not our most
pressing one.

15:57.540 --> 16:00.794
A major pharmaceutical
company has developed
a mutant antibody‒

16:00.877 --> 16:05.006
<i>- a way to suppress
the mutant "X" gene.</i>
- Suppress?

16:05.090 --> 16:08.760
Permanently.
They're calling it a cure.

16:13.306 --> 16:17.560
Well, that's ridiculous.
You can't cure being a mutant.
Well, scientifically speaking‒

16:17.644 --> 16:20.480
Since when did we become
a disease? How can anybody
in their right‒

16:20.563 --> 16:24.442
Storm.
They're announcing it now.

16:28.530 --> 16:32.867
These so-called mutants
are people just like us.

16:32.951 --> 16:35.787
Their affliction is
nothing more than a disease,

16:35.870 --> 16:39.207
a corruption of
healthy cellular activity.

16:39.290 --> 16:42.669
But I stand here today to
tell you there's hope.

16:42.752 --> 16:46.006
And this site,
once the world's
most famous prison,

16:46.089 --> 16:50.093
will now be
the source of freedom for
all mutants who choose it.

16:50.176 --> 16:54.222
Ladies and gentlemen,
I proudly present...

16:54.305 --> 16:56.683
the answer to mutation.

16:56.766 --> 17:00.186
Finally, we have a cure.

17:00.270 --> 17:03.732
<i>[Applause On TV]</i>

17:03.815 --> 17:08.486
Who would want this cure?
I mean, what kind of coward
would take it just to fit in?

17:08.569 --> 17:12.906
Is it cowardice to save
oneself from persecution?

17:12.991 --> 17:17.037
Not all of us can fit in so easily.
You don't shed on the furniture.

17:17.119 --> 17:20.165
<i>Well, for all we know,
the government helped
cook this up.</i>

17:20.248 --> 17:23.710
- I can assure you the government
had nothing to do with this.
- Well, I've heard that before.

17:23.792 --> 17:27.672
My boy, I have been
fighting for mutant rights
since before you had claws.

17:27.756 --> 17:29.758
Did he just call me "boy"?

17:29.841 --> 17:32.927
Is it true?
They can cure us?

17:33.011 --> 17:36.306
Yes, Rogue.
It appears to be true.

17:38.850 --> 17:42.896
<i>No, Professor.
They can't cure us.</i>

17:44.814 --> 17:47.609
You want to know why?
Because there's nothin' to cure.

17:47.692 --> 17:51.488
Nothing's wrong with you.
Or any of us, for that matter.

17:53.156 --> 17:57.869
<i>[Man]
How should we, as mutants,
respond? Here's what I think.</i>

17:57.952 --> 18:03.124
This is about getting organized,
bringing our complaints
to the right people.

18:03.208 --> 18:06.795
We need to put together
a committee and talk
to the government.

18:06.878 --> 18:08.838
[ Shouting ]

18:08.922 --> 18:12.967
<i>They don't understand.
They don't know what it
means to be a mutant.</i>

18:13.051 --> 18:18.932
<i>We need to show them,
educate them, let them know
that we're here to stay.</i>

18:19.015 --> 18:22.852
<i>[Man]
Come on.
People, you must listen.</i>

18:22.936 --> 18:26.523
- They won't take us seriously.
- They want to exterminate us.

18:26.606 --> 18:31.945
This cure is voluntary.
Nobody's talking about
extermination.

18:32.028 --> 18:34.155
<i>[Magneto]
No one ever talks about it.</i>

18:35.657 --> 18:38.201
They just do it.

18:38.284 --> 18:40.745
And you go on
with your lives,

18:40.829 --> 18:44.457
ignoring the signs
all around you.

18:44.541 --> 18:48.294
And then, one day,
when the air is still
and the night has fallen,

18:48.378 --> 18:51.005
- they come for you.
- Excuse me, but‒

18:51.089 --> 18:54.259
It's only then you realize,
while you were talking about
organizing and committees,

18:54.342 --> 18:56.553
the extermination
has already begun.

18:56.636 --> 19:01.266
Make no mistake, my brothers.
They will draw first blood.

19:01.349 --> 19:05.103
They will force
their cure upon us.

19:05.186 --> 19:10.191
The only question is, will you
join my brotherhood and fight...

19:10.275 --> 19:13.444
or wait for
the inevitable genocide?

19:13.528 --> 19:19.450
Who will you stand with‒
the humans... or us?

19:28.543 --> 19:30.920
You talk pretty tough
for a guy in a cape.

19:32.338 --> 19:34.674
Back off.

19:34.757 --> 19:37.760
If you're so proud
of being a mutant,
where's your mark?

19:40.471 --> 19:43.183
I have been
marked once, my dear,
and let me assure you...

19:43.266 --> 19:46.227
no needle shall ever
touch my skin again.

19:46.311 --> 19:50.899
You know who
you're talkin' to?
Do you?

19:53.401 --> 19:56.529
And what can you do?

19:56.613 --> 19:59.157
Hmm. So, you have talents.

19:59.240 --> 20:03.036
That and more.
I know you control metal.

20:03.119 --> 20:06.789
And I know there's 87
mutants in here and none
of them above a class three,

20:06.873 --> 20:09.542
other than you two.

20:11.002 --> 20:13.796
You can sense other mutants
and their powers?

20:13.880 --> 20:16.549
Mm-hmm.

20:16.633 --> 20:19.844
Could you locate one for me?

20:37.654 --> 20:39.781
<i>[President]
Let me out of here!</i>

20:39.864 --> 20:44.035
<i>I demand that you release me!
Do you know who I am?</i>

20:44.118 --> 20:46.162
I'm the president
of the United States.

20:46.246 --> 20:49.582
Oh, Mr. President.
Shut up!

20:51.626 --> 20:55.046
<i>[Little Girl]
Why are you doing this to me?
Let me down.</i>

20:55.129 --> 20:59.884
<i>I'll be a good girl.
Please, let me go. Please?</i>

20:59.968 --> 21:02.804
Keep it up. I'll spray you
in the face, bitch.

21:04.681 --> 21:09.769
When I get out of here,
I'm gonna kill you myself.

21:09.852 --> 21:12.313
[ Chuckles]
Yeah, right.

21:26.536 --> 21:29.706
<i>[Helicopter Whirring]</i>

21:40.341 --> 21:43.303
Secretary McCoy,
welcome to Worthington Labs.

21:43.386 --> 21:45.847
Thank you, Dr. Rao.
Not an easy place to get to.

21:45.930 --> 21:48.099
It's the safest location
we could find.

21:48.182 --> 21:50.643
That's why we keep
the source of the cure here.

21:50.727 --> 21:54.230
<i>He is a mutant.
You understand
our concern.</i>

21:54.314 --> 21:57.150
We are in full compliance
with your department's policy.

21:57.233 --> 21:59.152
How long will you
keep the boy here?

21:59.235 --> 22:02.864
Until we can fully map
his D.N.A. We can replicate it,
but we can't generate it.

22:02.947 --> 22:07.327
And his power,
what is its range?
You'll see.

22:07.410 --> 22:09.912
[ Game Beeping ]

22:10.997 --> 22:13.833
Jimmy?

22:13.916 --> 22:16.961
There's someone
I would like you to meet.

22:17.045 --> 22:19.005
Hello there, son.

22:19.088 --> 22:22.592
- Hi.
- My name is Hank McCoy.

22:29.307 --> 22:31.225
I'm sorry.

22:31.309 --> 22:34.270
It's okay.

22:43.071 --> 22:45.031
You have an amazing gift.

22:45.114 --> 22:47.075
<i>Thank you, Jimmy.</i>

22:51.871 --> 22:54.207
[ Game Beeps]

22:56.918 --> 23:00.171
Extraordinary,
isn't he?

23:00.254 --> 23:02.465
Yes, he is.

23:39.210 --> 23:43.047
<i>[Jean's Voice]
Scott.</i>

23:47.218 --> 23:52.890
[ Panting ]
<i>Scott.</i>

23:52.974 --> 23:55.393
<i>Scott. Scott.</i>

23:55.476 --> 23:58.604
<i>Can you hear me? I'm still here.
Scott. Scott.</i>

23:58.688 --> 24:00.606
Stop.
<i>I'm here, Scott!</i>

24:00.690 --> 24:02.608
Stop it.
<i>Scott.</i>

24:02.692 --> 24:05.027
<i>Scott. Scott!</i>
Stop it.

24:06.112 --> 24:10.491
- Scott! Scott!
- Stop!

25:07.215 --> 25:11.594
Jean?
Scott?

25:14.055 --> 25:16.098
How?

25:20.895 --> 25:22.980
I don't know.

25:37.662 --> 25:39.997
I want to see your eyes.

25:41.958 --> 25:45.878
Take these off.
No.

25:45.962 --> 25:48.047
No.

25:48.130 --> 25:51.759
Trust me.
I can control it now.

25:58.849 --> 26:02.478
Open them.
You can't hurt me.

26:30.256 --> 26:33.509
<i>[Xavier's Voice]
Scott. Scott. Scott. Scott.</i>

26:37.430 --> 26:39.432
What happened?
No clue!

26:39.515 --> 26:41.934
Professor, you okay?

26:42.018 --> 26:44.186
Get to Alkali Lake.

27:12.423 --> 27:16.010
You don't
want to be here.
Do you?

27:38.908 --> 27:41.369
I can't see a damn thing.

27:41.452 --> 27:43.871
I can take care
of that.

28:00.054 --> 28:02.056
What the‒

28:36.298 --> 28:38.634
<i>[Storm]
Logan!</i>

28:43.055 --> 28:46.350
Oh, God.
She's alive.

28:50.020 --> 28:52.022
Jean?

28:55.443 --> 29:00.614
<i>The sheer mass of water that
collapsed on top of Jean should
have obliterated her completely.</i>

29:00.698 --> 29:04.243
The only explanation of Jean's
survival is that her powers...

29:04.326 --> 29:07.830
wrapped her in a cocoon
of telekinetic energy.

29:08.956 --> 29:11.792
Is she gonna be okay?

29:11.876 --> 29:14.754
Jean Grey is the only class five
mutant I've ever encountered,

29:14.837 --> 29:16.839
her potential
practically limitless.

29:16.922 --> 29:20.426
<i>Her mutation is seated
in the unconscious part
of her mind,</i>

29:20.509 --> 29:22.428
<i>and therein lay the danger.</i>

29:22.511 --> 29:27.016
When she was a girl,
I created a series
of psychic barriers...

29:27.099 --> 29:29.685
<i>to isolate her powers
from her conscious mind.</i>

29:29.769 --> 29:33.522
<i>And, as a result,
Jean developed
a dual personality.</i>

29:33.606 --> 29:35.816
What?

29:35.900 --> 29:38.903
The conscious Jean,
whose powers were always
in her control...

29:38.986 --> 29:42.072
<i>and the dormant side,</i>

29:42.156 --> 29:45.451
a personality that,
in our sessions,

29:45.534 --> 29:48.037
came to call itself
the Phoenix‒

29:48.120 --> 29:52.124
a purely instinctual creature,
all desire and joy...

29:52.208 --> 29:54.460
and rage.

29:54.543 --> 29:57.254
She knew all this?

29:57.338 --> 29:59.840
It's unclear how much she knew.

29:59.924 --> 30:05.221
Far more critical is whether
the woman in front of us
is the Jean Grey we know...

30:05.304 --> 30:09.225
or the Phoenix
furiously struggling
to be free.

30:09.308 --> 30:11.811
She looks pretty peaceful to me.
Because I'm keeping her
that way.

30:11.894 --> 30:15.731
I'm trying to restore
the psychic blocks
and cage the beast again.

30:15.815 --> 30:18.651
What have you done to her?

30:18.734 --> 30:21.779
Logan,
you have to understand‒

30:21.862 --> 30:25.115
- You're talkin' about a person's
mind here, about Jean.
- She has to be controlled.

30:25.199 --> 30:29.745
Control? You know, sometimes
when you cage the beast,
the beast gets angry.

30:29.829 --> 30:34.542
You have no idea. You have no idea
of what she's capable.

30:34.625 --> 30:37.586
<i>No, Professor.
I had no idea what
you were capable of.</i>

30:37.670 --> 30:41.257
I had a terrible choice to make.
I chose the lesser of two evils.

30:41.340 --> 30:44.510
Well, it sounds to me
like Jean had no choice at all.

30:44.593 --> 30:48.097
I don't have to
explain myself,

30:48.180 --> 30:50.766
least of all to you.

30:57.982 --> 30:59.859
History will be
made here today.
[All Shouting ]

30:59.942 --> 31:04.071
For the first time,
the so-called "mutant cure"
will be available to the public.

31:04.154 --> 31:07.491
Now, reaction has run the gamut,
with mutants on both sides
of the line.

31:07.575 --> 31:09.618
<i>Some are desperate
for this cure,</i>

31:09.702 --> 31:12.913
<i>while others are offended
by the very idea of it.</i>

31:12.997 --> 31:15.416
<i>[Continues, Indistinct]</i>

31:27.011 --> 31:30.055
Is Secretary McCoy
going to be a problem?
Hard to say.

31:30.139 --> 31:34.518
His political views
seem somewhat at odds
with his personal issues.

31:34.602 --> 31:38.188
Excuse me, sir?
Your son's arrived.

31:38.272 --> 31:40.316
Good.
Bring him in.

31:40.399 --> 31:42.568
You sure you want to
start with him?

31:42.651 --> 31:45.029
I think
it's important, yes.

31:46.572 --> 31:49.116
<i>- [Dr. Rao] Hello, Warren.</i>
- How are you, Son?

31:49.199 --> 31:50.993
You sleep well?
Yeah.

31:51.076 --> 31:54.204
You know,
I'm proud of you
for doing this.

31:54.288 --> 31:58.500
Everything's gonna be fine.
I promise.
Yeah.

31:59.835 --> 32:01.837
You ready?

32:31.367 --> 32:33.911
The transformation
can be a little jarring.

32:38.832 --> 32:40.918
Dad, can we talk
about this for a sec?

32:41.001 --> 32:44.004
We've talked about it, Son.
It'll all be over soon.

32:44.088 --> 32:47.132
- [ Shudders ]
<i>- Everything's going to be fine.</i>

32:47.216 --> 32:49.510
Wait.

32:49.593 --> 32:53.389
- I can't do this.
- Warren, calm down.

32:53.472 --> 32:56.100
- No. I-I can't do this.
- Yes, you can.

32:56.183 --> 32:58.394
- Okay, just give me a minute‒
- Just relax, Son. Take it easy.

32:58.477 --> 33:01.146
- No! I can't do this!
- Calm down. I promise you,
it will be fine!

33:01.230 --> 33:03.232
Dad!
<i>Warren, relax!</i>

33:11.073 --> 33:16.161
Warren, it's a better life.
It's what we all want.

33:16.245 --> 33:19.248
No. It's what you want.

33:21.500 --> 33:24.128
Warren! No!

33:28.966 --> 33:31.760
[ Screaming ]

34:28.317 --> 34:30.319
[ Groaning ]

34:37.701 --> 34:40.829
[ Cracks ]
Told you so.

34:56.303 --> 35:00.140
- About time.
- I've been busy.

35:00.224 --> 35:02.142
Did you find what
you were looking for?

35:02.226 --> 35:05.479
The source of the cure
is a mutant, a child
at Worthington Labs.

35:05.562 --> 35:08.315
<i>Without him,
they have nothing.</i>

35:08.398 --> 35:11.193
Read off the guest list.

35:11.276 --> 35:15.864
<i>Cell 41205.
James Madrox.</i>

35:15.948 --> 35:18.033
This one robbed seven banks...

35:23.956 --> 35:28.043
- at the same time.
- I could use a man
of your talents.

35:29.128 --> 35:31.880
I'm in.
Welcome to the Brotherhood.

35:35.050 --> 35:39.555
Careful with this one.
Cain Marko.
Solitary confinement.

35:39.638 --> 35:43.642
Now, check this out.
"Prisoner must be confined
at all times.

35:43.725 --> 35:48.397
<i>- If he builds any momentum,
no object can stop him."</i>
- How fascinating.

35:51.233 --> 35:54.236
- And what do they call you?
- Juggernaut.

35:54.319 --> 35:58.448
- I can't imagine why.
- You gonna let me out of here?
I need to pee.

36:06.248 --> 36:08.250
[ Rumbling ]

36:10.294 --> 36:13.463
- Nice helmet.
- Keeps my face pretty.

36:13.547 --> 36:18.302
<i>- [Magneto] I think he'll make
a fine addition to our army.
- [Pyro] Yeah.</i>

36:18.385 --> 36:20.387
No!

36:26.560 --> 36:29.813
[ Groaning ]

36:45.662 --> 36:48.498
You saved me.

36:52.002 --> 36:53.795
Eric?

36:56.173 --> 36:58.926
I'm sorry, my dear.

36:59.009 --> 37:01.637
You're not
one of us anymore.

37:07.226 --> 37:10.312
Such a shame.
She was so beautiful.

37:16.485 --> 37:20.364
You think resigning's gonna
make a difference? That's
no way to influence policy.

37:20.447 --> 37:23.116
Policy is being made
without me, Mr. President.

37:23.200 --> 37:26.328
The decision to
turn the cure into a weapon
was made without me.

37:26.411 --> 37:30.165
<i>What happened on that
convoy was inexcusable.
But your actions‒</i>

37:30.249 --> 37:33.502
Hank, that was
an isolated incident.
You have to understand.

37:33.585 --> 37:35.545
Those mutants
were a real threat.

37:35.629 --> 37:38.507
Have you even begun to think
what a slippery slope you're on?

37:38.590 --> 37:41.343
I have.

37:43.804 --> 37:48.850
And I worry about how
democracy survives when one man
can move cities with his mind.

37:48.934 --> 37:50.936
As do I.

37:54.231 --> 37:56.984
You and I know that it's
only going to get worse.

37:57.067 --> 38:00.195
All the more reason why
I need to be where I belong.

38:02.489 --> 38:06.326
[ Beeping ]

38:29.099 --> 38:31.977
Jean.

38:34.813 --> 38:38.942
- Hey, Logan.
- Welcome back.

38:40.569 --> 38:42.571
Back where we first met.

38:42.654 --> 38:46.950
<i>Only I was in your place
and you were in mine.</i>

38:47.034 --> 38:49.077
You okay?

38:51.246 --> 38:53.248
Yeah.

38:55.584 --> 38:58.253
More than okay.

39:09.973 --> 39:12.934
Logan, you're making me blush.

39:14.186 --> 39:17.314
- Are you reading my thoughts?
- I don't have to.

39:20.776 --> 39:22.903
It's okay.

39:36.416 --> 39:39.294
It's okay.

39:47.719 --> 39:50.138
[ Monitors Whirring ]

40:02.150 --> 40:04.945
[ Groans]

40:17.999 --> 40:19.626
- Wait.
- No.

40:25.382 --> 40:30.887
Jean,
this isn't you.
Yes. Yes, it is me.

40:30.971 --> 40:35.225
No. Maybe you ought to
take it easy, huh?

40:35.308 --> 40:38.395
The professor said
you might be...

40:38.478 --> 40:41.273
different.

40:41.356 --> 40:43.483
He would know, wouldn't he?

40:43.567 --> 40:45.902
What?

40:45.986 --> 40:51.158
You think he's not
in your head too?
Look at you, Logan.

40:51.241 --> 40:54.244
He's tamed you.

40:57.330 --> 40:59.541
Where's Scott?

41:02.127 --> 41:03.962
Jean?

41:04.045 --> 41:07.132
Where am I?

41:07.215 --> 41:09.259
You're in the mansion.

41:09.342 --> 41:12.929
You need to tell me
what happened to Scott.

41:16.808 --> 41:19.394
Jean, tell me
what happened to him.

41:31.323 --> 41:35.410
- Oh, God.
<i>- [Creaking]</i>

41:40.457 --> 41:42.250
Look at me.

41:44.669 --> 41:46.630
Jean, stay with me.

41:47.756 --> 41:51.092
Talk to me.
Look at me. Look at me!
No.

41:51.176 --> 41:53.053
- Focus! Focus, Jean!
- [ Rattling Stops ]

41:54.596 --> 41:58.308
Kill me.
What?

41:58.391 --> 42:00.769
Kill me before
I kill someone else.
Don't say that.

42:00.852 --> 42:03.230
Please.
Stop it.

42:03.313 --> 42:05.941
Kill me.

42:07.025 --> 42:09.319
Stop it. Look at me.
Look at me.Jean.

42:09.402 --> 42:12.113
It'll be all right.
We can help you.

42:12.197 --> 42:15.700
Okay?
The professor can help.
He can fix it.

42:15.784 --> 42:17.786
I don't want to fix it!

42:29.005 --> 42:34.135
Voluntary?
They put the cure in a gun.

42:34.219 --> 42:36.429
I told you they would
draw first blood.

42:36.513 --> 42:39.683
- So what do we do?
- What do we do?

42:39.766 --> 42:43.853
We use this weapon
as a lightning rod to bring
countless more to our cause.

42:45.230 --> 42:48.483
Come. We have
an army to build.

42:51.152 --> 42:55.448
I picked something up.
An electromagnetic force.

42:55.532 --> 42:59.035
It's massive.
It's... a mutant.

42:59.119 --> 43:03.790
Class five.
More powerful than anything
I've ever felt.

43:03.873 --> 43:06.209
More powerful than you.

43:09.045 --> 43:11.172
Where is she?

43:13.842 --> 43:16.094
Logan?

43:16.177 --> 43:18.471
Jean? Jean!
What happened?

43:18.555 --> 43:20.849
What have you done?

43:24.894 --> 43:27.772
- I think she killed Scott.
- What?

43:30.025 --> 43:34.529
- That's not possible.
- I warned you.

43:38.491 --> 43:41.661
She's left the mansion,
but she's trying to
block my thoughts.

43:41.745 --> 43:44.039
She's so strong.

43:46.041 --> 43:48.043
It may be too late.

43:52.714 --> 43:54.633
Wait for me here.
What?

43:54.716 --> 43:57.469
I need to see Jean alone.

43:57.552 --> 44:01.264
<i>[Magneto]
You were right, Charles.
This one is special.</i>

44:01.348 --> 44:03.308
What the hell
are you doing here?

44:03.391 --> 44:06.311
The same as the professor.
Visiting an old friend.

44:06.394 --> 44:08.647
I don't want trouble here.
Nor do I, Charles.

44:08.730 --> 44:11.232
So, shall we go inside?

44:13.193 --> 44:17.322
I came to bring Jean home.
Don't interfere, Eric.
Just like old times, huh?

44:17.405 --> 44:20.825
She needs help.
Jean is not well.

44:20.909 --> 44:24.621
Funny. You sound
just like her parents.

44:24.704 --> 44:26.873
Nobody gets inside.

45:12.961 --> 45:17.257
I knew you'd come.
Of course. I've come
to bring you home.

45:17.340 --> 45:19.509
I have no home.
Yes, you do.

45:19.592 --> 45:21.678
You have a home
and a family.

45:21.761 --> 45:26.266
- He thinks your power is
too great for you to control.
- Eric.

45:26.349 --> 45:28.893
I don't believe
your mind games are going
to work anymore, Charles.

45:28.977 --> 45:31.521
So you want to control me?
No.

45:31.604 --> 45:33.940
He does.
No.
I want to help you.

45:34.023 --> 45:38.278
Help me?
What's wrong with me?

45:38.361 --> 45:40.321
- Absolutely nothing.
- Eric, stop!

45:40.405 --> 45:43.408
No, Charles! Not this time!
You've always held her back!

45:43.491 --> 45:46.619
For your own good, Jean.

45:46.703 --> 45:49.038
Stay out of my head.

45:49.122 --> 45:52.041
[ Rattling ]

45:52.125 --> 45:55.837
I'm goin' in.
The professor said
he'd handle this.

46:02.051 --> 46:06.055
Look at me, Jean. I can
help you. Look at me!
No.

46:06.139 --> 46:09.768
Get out of my head.

46:09.851 --> 46:12.937
- Perhaps you should
listen to her, Charles.
- You must trust me.

46:13.021 --> 46:16.483
You're a danger to
everyone and yourself!
But I can help you!

46:16.566 --> 46:19.611
- I think you want to give her the cure!
- Look what happened to Scott!

46:19.694 --> 46:23.531
<i>You killed the man you love
because you couldn't control
your power!</i>

46:23.615 --> 46:25.533
No! Stop it!

46:27.410 --> 46:29.704
- That's it.
- [ Growls]

46:32.499 --> 46:35.543
[ Shouting ]

46:53.853 --> 46:56.606
[ Chuckles]

47:11.621 --> 47:14.207
Jean, let me in.

48:09.012 --> 48:11.472
[ Groans]

48:16.728 --> 48:19.647
<i>No, Jean!
Jean!</i>

49:19.415 --> 49:21.918
Don't let it control you.

49:26.547 --> 49:29.133
[ Shouts]

49:30.885 --> 49:32.679
Charles!

49:59.122 --> 50:02.500
My dear, come with me.

50:21.477 --> 50:23.813
Oh, God!

50:23.896 --> 50:26.733
- [ Sobbing ]
- No.

50:58.806 --> 51:01.309
<i>[Storm]
We live in an age of darkness,</i>

51:01.392 --> 51:04.062
<i>a world full of fear,</i>

51:04.145 --> 51:07.398
<i>hate and intolerance.</i>

51:07.482 --> 51:11.903
<i>But in every age,
there are those
who fight against it.</i>

51:11.986 --> 51:17.200
<i>Charles Xavier was born
into a world divided,</i>

51:17.283 --> 51:20.620
a world he tried to heal‒

51:20.703 --> 51:23.623
a mission he never
saw accomplished.

51:23.706 --> 51:29.462
It seems the destiny
of great men to see
their goals unfulfilled.

51:29.545 --> 51:32.840
<i>Charles was more than a leader,
more than a teacher.</i>

51:32.924 --> 51:34.842
<i>He was a friend.</i>

51:34.926 --> 51:38.513
<i>When we were afraid,
he gave us strength.</i>

51:38.596 --> 51:42.517
<i>And when we were alone,
he gave us a family.</i>

51:43.601 --> 51:46.938
He may be gone,
but his teachings...

51:47.021 --> 51:50.775
<i>live on through us,
his students.</i>

51:50.858 --> 51:54.445
<i>Wherever we may go,
we must carry on his vision.</i>

51:54.529 --> 51:58.699
And that's a vision
of a world united.

52:14.674 --> 52:17.093
[ Sniffles]

52:19.554 --> 52:22.473
<i>[Knocking]</i>

52:22.557 --> 52:25.184
<i>[Bobby]
Kitty?</i>

52:25.268 --> 52:27.353
Bobby?

52:29.897 --> 52:32.400
- You okay?
- Yeah.

52:36.404 --> 52:38.739
Ah, it's just...

52:38.823 --> 52:41.868
Xavier came to my house.

52:41.951 --> 52:44.453
He was the one that
convinced me to come here.

52:44.537 --> 52:48.332
Yeah, me too.
We're all feelin'
the same way, you know.

52:48.416 --> 52:51.335
No, Bobby, we're not.

52:51.419 --> 52:53.713
You have Rogue and I have‒

52:55.464 --> 52:58.259
You know,
I‒ I just miss home.

52:58.342 --> 53:01.429
The first snow
and all of that.

53:04.223 --> 53:08.019
- Kitty, get up. Come with me.
- Storm told us to stay in our rooms.

53:08.102 --> 53:11.981
Don't worry. We won't get
caught. I mean, you can walk
through walls, you know.

53:12.064 --> 53:14.734
[ Chuckles ]
<i>Come on.</i>

53:26.829 --> 53:28.831
This place
can be home too.

53:51.687 --> 53:54.398
[ Both Laughing ]

53:54.482 --> 53:56.442
Bobby. Bobby!
Okay. Come on.

53:56.525 --> 53:58.486
Whoa!

54:07.787 --> 54:09.789
Thank you
for this, Bobby.

54:11.415 --> 54:14.293
[ Scoffs]

54:27.682 --> 54:29.892
You need
a lift, kid?

54:29.976 --> 54:32.144
No.

54:33.854 --> 54:35.856
Where're you going?

54:37.358 --> 54:39.860
You don't know
what it's like to be
afraid of your powers,

54:39.944 --> 54:42.405
to be afraid
to get close to anybody.

54:42.488 --> 54:44.740
Yeah, I do.

54:44.824 --> 54:48.244
I wanna be able
to touch people, Logan.

54:49.745 --> 54:54.041
A hug, a handshake,
a kiss.

54:54.125 --> 54:57.044
I hope you're not
doing this for some boy.

54:59.964 --> 55:03.634
Look, if you
wanna go, then go.

55:03.718 --> 55:05.720
Just be sure
it's what you want.

55:08.139 --> 55:13.019
Shouldn't you
be telling me to stay,
to go upstairs and unpack?

55:13.102 --> 55:15.187
I'm not your father.
I'm your friend.

55:18.691 --> 55:21.444
Think about
what I said, Rogue.

55:21.527 --> 55:24.155
Marie.

55:24.238 --> 55:26.532
Marie.

55:58.397 --> 56:00.316
<i>[Footsteps Approaching]</i>

56:04.403 --> 56:07.448
Do you remember
when we first met?

56:07.531 --> 56:10.826
Do you know
what I saw when
I looked at you?

56:10.910 --> 56:14.497
I saw the next stage
in evolution,

56:14.580 --> 56:18.376
what Charles and I
dreamt of finding.

56:18.459 --> 56:21.253
And I thought to myself,
"Why would Charles...

56:21.337 --> 56:24.673
want to turn this goddess
into a mortal?"

56:29.178 --> 56:34.767
I can manipulate
the metal in this,
but you‒

56:34.850 --> 56:39.480
you can do anything,
anything you can think of.

56:49.949 --> 56:51.909
Jean‒

56:51.992 --> 56:53.953
Enough.

56:55.538 --> 56:57.498
Enough!

57:00.000 --> 57:03.337
You sound
just like him.
Jean,

57:03.421 --> 57:06.715
he wanted to
hold you back.
What do you want?

57:06.799 --> 57:09.343
I want you
to be what you are,

57:09.427 --> 57:12.388
as nature intended.

57:14.056 --> 57:16.142
That cure is meant
for all of us.

57:16.225 --> 57:20.271
If we want freedom,
we must fight for it.

57:21.772 --> 57:24.066
And that fight
begins now.

57:32.825 --> 57:35.494
<i>She shouldn't
be here with us.</i>

57:35.578 --> 57:37.913
Her power's
completely unstable.

57:37.997 --> 57:41.292
Only in the wrong hands.
You trust her?
She's one of them.

57:41.375 --> 57:44.295
So were you once.
I stuck with you
all the way.

57:44.378 --> 57:47.214
I would've killed
the professor if you'd
given me the chance.

57:49.008 --> 57:53.095
Charles Xavier
did more for mutants
than you'll ever know.

57:53.179 --> 57:57.975
My single greatest regret
is that he had to die
for our dream to live.

58:14.867 --> 58:17.703
So what now?
What do we do?

58:17.786 --> 58:21.332
Professor Xavier started
this school, perhaps it's best
that it end with him.

58:21.415 --> 58:23.375
We'll have to tell the students
they're going home.

58:23.459 --> 58:25.419
Must of us don't have
anywhere to go.

58:27.463 --> 58:31.050
I can't believe this.
I can't believe we're not
gonna fight for this school.

58:38.307 --> 58:41.060
<i>I'm sorry. I know
this is a bad time.</i>

58:41.143 --> 58:44.104
I was told that this was
a safe place for mutants.

58:45.272 --> 58:47.274
It was, son.

58:51.362 --> 58:55.074
And it still is.
We'll find you a room.

58:55.157 --> 58:58.118
Hank, tell all the students
this school stays open.

59:13.634 --> 59:15.553
Rogue.

59:16.637 --> 59:18.556
Hey, Rogue.

59:27.731 --> 59:29.733
<i>Hey, Pete,
you seen Rogue?</i>

59:29.817 --> 59:31.819
Yeah, she took off.

59:45.624 --> 59:47.710
<i>[Jean's Voice]
Logan.</i>

59:47.793 --> 59:49.920
<i>Logan!</i>

59:50.004 --> 59:52.506
<i>Logan.</i>
Jean?

59:52.590 --> 59:54.717
<i>Logan, where am I?
Logan!</i>

59:54.800 --> 59:56.719
<i>Logan.
Logan. Logan.</i>

59:56.802 --> 59:59.638
God!
[ Groans]
<i>Logan!</i>

59:59.722 --> 01:00:02.349
<i>Logan. Logan. Logan.</i>

01:00:21.994 --> 01:00:24.830
Where are you goin'?
Where do you think?

01:00:24.913 --> 01:00:27.124
She's gone, Logan.
She's not comin' back.

01:00:27.207 --> 01:00:30.210
- You don't know that.
- She killed the professor.

01:00:30.294 --> 01:00:34.548
It wasn't Jean.
The Jean I know
is still in there.

01:00:34.632 --> 01:00:36.842
<i>Listen‒</i>
Outta my way.

01:00:36.925 --> 01:00:40.304
Why can't you see
the truth, huh? Why can't
you just let her go?

01:00:40.387 --> 01:00:42.306
Because‒

01:00:42.389 --> 01:00:44.391
Because‒
Because you love her.

01:00:54.818 --> 01:00:57.446
She made her choice.
Now it's time we make ours.

01:00:57.529 --> 01:00:59.907
So if you're with us,
then be with us.

01:01:13.962 --> 01:01:17.466
[ Chanting ]
We don't need a cure!
We don't need a cure!

01:01:29.603 --> 01:01:32.564
Gettin' the cure
so you can go back home
to Mommy and Daddy?

01:01:34.608 --> 01:01:37.236
I'm lookin' for someone.

01:01:37.319 --> 01:01:39.321
<i>[John]
Oh, I get it.</i>

01:01:39.405 --> 01:01:41.782
Your girlfriend.

01:01:42.908 --> 01:01:44.827
I figured
she'd want the cure.

01:01:44.910 --> 01:01:46.829
She's pathetic.

01:01:50.999 --> 01:01:53.293
Come on, Iceman.

01:01:54.795 --> 01:01:56.755
Make a move.

01:02:02.219 --> 01:02:04.388
Same old Bobby.

01:02:04.471 --> 01:02:06.473
Still afraid of a fight!

01:02:12.020 --> 01:02:13.981
[ Clamoring ]

01:02:18.318 --> 01:02:21.447
<i>[Magneto]
Today's attack
was only our first salvo.</i>

01:02:21.530 --> 01:02:25.576
So long as the cure exists,
our war will rage.

01:02:25.659 --> 01:02:29.496
Your cities will not be safe.
Your streets will not be safe.

01:02:29.580 --> 01:02:31.957
<i>You will not be safe.</i>

01:02:32.040 --> 01:02:35.961
And to my fellow mutants,
I make you this offer‒

01:02:36.044 --> 01:02:38.839
<i>join us or stay out
of our way.</i>

01:02:38.922 --> 01:02:42.092
Enough mutant blood
has been spilled already.

01:02:43.469 --> 01:02:47.139
We're tryin' to track him, sir.
We're working hard.

01:02:49.600 --> 01:02:51.560
We cannot let him do this.

01:02:51.643 --> 01:02:53.937
You know I agree, sir.

01:02:54.021 --> 01:02:56.356
This is now
a national security matter.

01:02:56.440 --> 01:02:58.358
Seize and secure
Worthington Labs.

01:02:58.442 --> 01:03:01.904
I want troops armed with cure
weapons deployed immediately.
Yes, sir.

01:03:01.987 --> 01:03:05.657
And, Trask,
you have to find Magneto
and stop him,

01:03:05.741 --> 01:03:08.285
by any means necessary.

01:03:08.368 --> 01:03:11.580
Magneto wants a war.
We'll give him one.

01:03:11.663 --> 01:03:14.458
<i>[Man]
Let's go! Keep it movin '!</i>

01:03:14.541 --> 01:03:18.045
<i>Turn in your old weapon.
Turn in all metal‒</i>

01:03:18.128 --> 01:03:21.715
<i>bayonets, magazines, dog tags.</i>

01:03:21.799 --> 01:03:24.218
<i>Pick up your plastic weapons.</i>

01:03:24.301 --> 01:03:28.180
<i>Pick up your cure cartridge.
Absolutely no metal.</i>

01:03:33.811 --> 01:03:36.230
[ Clamoring ]

01:03:38.273 --> 01:03:42.820
<i>[Crowd Chanting]
We don't need a cure.
We don't need a cure.</i>

01:04:10.973 --> 01:04:13.433
[ Sniffs]

01:04:40.168 --> 01:04:42.462
<i>[Spikes Swishing]</i>

01:06:00.749 --> 01:06:03.919
<i>[Crowd Cheering]</i>

01:06:04.002 --> 01:06:06.713
<i>- [Magneto]
Members of the Brotherhood‒</i>
- [ Cheering ]

01:06:12.260 --> 01:06:14.304
They wish to cure us.
[Jeering ]

01:06:14.388 --> 01:06:17.432
But I say to you,
we are the cure!

01:06:17.516 --> 01:06:20.602
[ Cheering ]

01:06:20.686 --> 01:06:23.689
<i>The cure for their infirm,
imperfect condition called...</i>

01:06:23.772 --> 01:06:25.732
Homo sapiens.

01:06:27.776 --> 01:06:30.862
They have their weapons.

01:06:30.946 --> 01:06:32.906
We have ours.

01:06:34.783 --> 01:06:38.412
We will strike
with a vengeance and a fury...

01:06:38.495 --> 01:06:41.415
<i>that this world
has never witnessed.</i>

01:06:43.291 --> 01:06:49.089
And if any mutants
stand in our way, we will
use this poison against them.

01:06:49.172 --> 01:06:52.509
<i>We shall go to
Alcatraz Island,</i>

01:06:52.592 --> 01:06:54.803
<i>take control of the cure...</i>

01:06:54.886 --> 01:06:57.514
<i>and destroy its source.</i>

01:06:57.597 --> 01:07:01.685
<i>And then,
nothing can stop us!</i>

01:07:01.768 --> 01:07:04.312
<i>[Cheering]</i>

01:07:16.283 --> 01:07:18.118
<i>Jean?</i>

01:07:25.000 --> 01:07:26.918
[ Groans]

01:07:29.921 --> 01:07:33.842
<i>I know the smell
of your adamantium
from a mile a way.</i>

01:07:33.925 --> 01:07:35.886
I didn't come here
to fight you.

01:07:35.969 --> 01:07:38.346
- Smart boy.
- I came for Jean.

01:07:38.430 --> 01:07:40.640
You think I'm keeping her
against her will?

01:07:46.229 --> 01:07:48.190
[ Groaning ]

01:07:51.401 --> 01:07:53.487
She's here because
she wants to be.

01:07:53.570 --> 01:07:56.406
You don't know
what you're dealing with.
I know full well.

01:07:56.490 --> 01:07:58.909
I saw what
she did to Charles.

01:07:58.992 --> 01:08:02.496
And you just stood there
and let him die?

01:08:02.579 --> 01:08:04.456
I'm not leaving here
without her.

01:08:04.539 --> 01:08:06.541
Yes, you are.

01:08:08.043 --> 01:08:10.462
Whoa‒

01:08:19.638 --> 01:08:22.557
Okay.

01:08:22.640 --> 01:08:24.768
Two minutes to
rendezvous, Mr. President.

01:08:27.562 --> 01:08:30.982
<i>We have a satellite feed
of Magneto's base of operations.</i>

01:08:34.528 --> 01:08:38.573
<i>- How did we find it?</i>
- She gave us everything
we wanted and more.

01:08:38.657 --> 01:08:40.617
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

01:08:40.700 --> 01:08:43.578
Hell hath no fury
like a woman scorned.

01:09:18.697 --> 01:09:20.907
<i>[Man Over Radio]
Approaching target dead ahead.</i>

01:09:22.408 --> 01:09:24.911
<i>Set for 360-degree incursion.</i>

01:09:37.299 --> 01:09:41.051
This is Team Leader
to Bravo One.
We are green to go.

01:09:44.680 --> 01:09:47.725
Okay.
Send them in.

01:09:47.809 --> 01:09:49.019
Okay.

01:09:49.102 --> 01:09:51.229
Freeze, mutants!
Get your hands in the air!

01:09:51.313 --> 01:09:53.564
<i>[Clamoring]</i>

01:10:07.996 --> 01:10:11.625
Okay. I give up.

01:10:11.708 --> 01:10:14.044
<i>[ Team Leader]
Sorry, Mr. Secretary.
It was a decoy.</i>

01:10:14.127 --> 01:10:17.130
If he's not there,
then where the hell is he?

01:10:25.472 --> 01:10:29.517
Worthington Labs.
It ends where it began.

01:10:29.601 --> 01:10:31.561
Are you sure
the boy's still inside?

01:10:31.645 --> 01:10:34.564
100%.
So how we supposed
to get there?

01:10:34.648 --> 01:10:36.775
'Cause I don't swim.

01:10:36.858 --> 01:10:39.152
Leave that to me.

01:10:44.658 --> 01:10:47.911
Storm? Storm?
<i>[Door Opens]</i>

01:10:47.994 --> 01:10:50.789
<i>What are you doing
back here?</i>

01:10:50.872 --> 01:10:52.874
I need help.

01:10:52.958 --> 01:10:55.752
You found her.
<i>Yeah.
She's with Magneto.</i>

01:10:55.835 --> 01:10:57.879
Where are they?
They're on the move.

01:10:57.963 --> 01:11:00.215
I know where they're going.
You're saying
you saw Magneto?

01:11:00.298 --> 01:11:03.510
Yeah. Gotta go now.
They're going to
attack Alcatraz.

01:11:03.593 --> 01:11:05.804
[ Hank]
There are troops
stationed on that island.

01:11:05.887 --> 01:11:08.848
<i>[Logan]
Not enough to stop him.
[Storm] Let's suit up.</i>

01:11:13.770 --> 01:11:15.689
I don't believe
this once fit me.

01:11:15.772 --> 01:11:18.441
If Magneto gets ahold
of that cure, there will
be no stopping him.

01:11:18.525 --> 01:11:20.610
Can you estimate
how many he has?
An army.

01:11:20.694 --> 01:11:23.405
And Jean.
His powers have limits,
hers do not.

01:11:23.488 --> 01:11:25.532
[ Bobby]
There's only
six of us, Logan.

01:11:28.618 --> 01:11:32.580
Yeah. We're outnumbered.
I'm not gonna lie to you.

01:11:33.873 --> 01:11:37.419
But we lost Scott.
We lost the professor.

01:11:37.502 --> 01:11:41.673
<i>If we don't fight now,
everything they stood for
will die with them.</i>

01:11:43.508 --> 01:11:46.177
I'm not gonna
let that happen.

01:11:46.261 --> 01:11:48.263
Are you?

01:11:49.639 --> 01:11:51.599
Then we stand together,

01:11:53.143 --> 01:11:56.396
X-Men, all of us.

01:12:03.820 --> 01:12:07.532
We're in.
Let's go.

01:12:12.537 --> 01:12:14.456
They're ready.

01:12:14.539 --> 01:12:17.542
Yeah, I know.
But are you ready...

01:12:17.625 --> 01:12:20.462
to do what you need to do
when the time comes?

01:13:36.371 --> 01:13:38.790
[ Metal Warping ]

01:13:44.003 --> 01:13:45.839
<i>[Rumbling]</i>
[ Clamoring ]

01:13:49.050 --> 01:13:51.719
Dad, what's going on?

01:13:52.846 --> 01:13:55.682
It's an earthquake.

01:13:58.393 --> 01:14:00.979
We're trapped!

01:14:06.609 --> 01:14:08.528
[ Screaming ]

01:14:55.909 --> 01:14:57.869
Cheese‒

01:15:07.879 --> 01:15:10.048
[ Screaming Continues]

01:16:04.227 --> 01:16:08.022
Charles always wanted
to build bridges.

01:16:22.745 --> 01:16:25.456
My God!

01:16:50.064 --> 01:16:53.651
<i>[Man] Fall back!
Take cover! Fall back!</i>

01:17:02.952 --> 01:17:04.871
[ Men Shouting ]

01:17:08.416 --> 01:17:14.130
The boy's in the southeast
corner of the building.
Well done.

01:17:14.213 --> 01:17:17.383
Let's take it down!
[ Cheering ]

01:17:33.232 --> 01:17:36.027
In chess,
the pawns go first.

01:17:38.613 --> 01:17:41.240
Humans and their guns.

01:17:50.083 --> 01:17:52.919
Plastic.
They've learned.

01:17:59.092 --> 01:18:01.928
That's why the pawns go first.

01:18:09.185 --> 01:18:10.687
[ Screams]

01:18:10.770 --> 01:18:12.438
Target the bridge!

01:18:12.522 --> 01:18:14.148
[ Man ]
Bring out the launcher!

01:18:14.232 --> 01:18:16.943
- This is it!
- Ready! Load!

01:18:20.738 --> 01:18:22.615
Fire!

01:18:29.372 --> 01:18:31.791
Arclight,
use your shock waves!

01:18:31.874 --> 01:18:34.252
Target those weapons!

01:18:53.479 --> 01:18:56.065
<i>Oh, my stars and garters.</i>

01:18:56.149 --> 01:18:58.151
Goin' to stealth mode.

01:18:59.694 --> 01:19:02.071
<i>[President]
What about jets, tanks?</i>

01:19:02.155 --> 01:19:04.699
Against Magneto?
He'll turn 'em inside out.

01:19:04.782 --> 01:19:08.494
- Where are our ground troops?
<i>- Thirty minutes away.</i>

01:19:08.578 --> 01:19:11.456
Then God help us.

01:19:19.297 --> 01:19:20.631
[ Screaming ]

01:19:20.715 --> 01:19:22.967
They're coming for him.

01:19:25.762 --> 01:19:27.430
[ Man ] Get the humans!

01:19:27.513 --> 01:19:30.391
<i>[Jet Approaching]</i>

01:19:53.873 --> 01:19:55.917
Whoa!

01:19:57.126 --> 01:19:59.045
Don't ever
do that again.

01:20:05.885 --> 01:20:10.056
You men, cover the doors!
Everybody, get together!

01:20:10.139 --> 01:20:12.725
And hold this line!

01:20:26.656 --> 01:20:30.201
Traitors to their own cause.

01:20:36.332 --> 01:20:39.043
Finish them!

01:21:14.203 --> 01:21:15.913
Not yet.

01:21:30.636 --> 01:21:33.389
Go inside,
get the boy and kill him.

01:21:33.472 --> 01:21:35.433
With pleasure.

01:21:41.355 --> 01:21:44.025
Hold it!
[ Groaning ]

01:21:45.902 --> 01:21:49.155
- He's going for the boy!
- Not if I get there first!

01:21:50.156 --> 01:21:51.657
Kitty!

01:22:02.793 --> 01:22:05.546
Come on!

01:22:08.007 --> 01:22:10.009
Grow those back.

01:22:20.102 --> 01:22:22.855
Don't you know who I am?

01:22:24.106 --> 01:22:26.233
I'm the Juggernaut, bitch!

01:22:57.306 --> 01:22:59.225
Going somewhere?

01:23:03.187 --> 01:23:05.606
You're the guy that
invented the cure, right?

01:23:05.690 --> 01:23:07.900
Yes, I am.

01:23:09.360 --> 01:23:11.112
Girls?

01:23:11.195 --> 01:23:13.239
<i>No! Don't!
Don't hurt him!</i>

01:23:13.322 --> 01:23:16.867
- No! Don't hurt him!
<i>- Let go of me! I didn't do anything.</i>

01:23:16.951 --> 01:23:18.577
Calm down.
Calm down.

01:23:18.661 --> 01:23:21.288
Everything's
gonna be okay.

01:23:39.056 --> 01:23:40.975
I thought
you were a diplomat.

01:23:41.058 --> 01:23:43.811
As Churchill said, "There comes
a time when all men must‒"

01:23:45.104 --> 01:23:47.064
Oh, you get the point!

01:23:48.357 --> 01:23:52.820
Oh, no! No. Please!
No, no, don't! No!

01:23:58.993 --> 01:24:02.329
No, don't worry.
I'm here to help you.
I'm gonna get you out of here.

01:24:03.831 --> 01:24:06.083
<i>[Crash]</i>
This way.

01:24:07.334 --> 01:24:09.253
Oh, my God.
What's going on?

01:24:09.336 --> 01:24:11.547
Your powers
won't work with me.

01:24:11.630 --> 01:24:13.466
<i>[Crash]</i>

01:24:15.843 --> 01:24:18.596
Stay close,
all right?
Okay.

01:24:21.307 --> 01:24:24.268
I'm the wrong guy
to play hide-and-seek with.

01:24:24.351 --> 01:24:27.980
- Who's hiding, dickhead?
- [ Roars]

01:24:38.324 --> 01:24:42.870
Don't!
No! Don't! D‒

01:24:42.953 --> 01:24:46.832
Please, don't do this!
I only wanted to help
you people.

01:24:46.916 --> 01:24:49.460
Do we look like
we need your help?

01:25:19.949 --> 01:25:22.368
It's time to end this war.

01:25:32.294 --> 01:25:34.505
Take cover!

01:25:37.091 --> 01:25:39.218
<i>[Man]
Get out of the way!</i>

01:25:49.728 --> 01:25:51.397
<i>[Man]
Come on! Let's go!</i>

01:25:54.191 --> 01:25:55.776
<i>Go! Go! Go!</i>

01:26:08.164 --> 01:26:10.082
<i>[Man Screaming]</i>

01:26:12.918 --> 01:26:14.587
<i>[Man Screaming]</i>

01:26:44.241 --> 01:26:46.160
We work as a team.

01:26:47.494 --> 01:26:49.455
Best defense
is a good offense.

01:26:52.875 --> 01:26:55.085
Run!

01:26:56.629 --> 01:26:58.964
Bobby! You think you can
take out your old friend?

01:27:12.311 --> 01:27:14.230
Go ahead.

01:27:15.731 --> 01:27:17.733
Storm, we're gonna
need some cover.

01:27:17.816 --> 01:27:19.777
Right.

01:28:08.993 --> 01:28:12.079
You're in over
your head, Bobby.

01:28:12.162 --> 01:28:14.415
Maybe you should
go back to school.

01:28:25.467 --> 01:28:28.262
You never should've left.

01:28:29.513 --> 01:28:31.724
<i>[Logan]
This is it.</i>

01:28:31.807 --> 01:28:35.561
Hey. Make it a strike.

01:28:40.607 --> 01:28:42.568
[ Groaning ]

01:28:47.531 --> 01:28:50.075
You never learn, do you?

01:28:51.744 --> 01:28:55.205
Actually, I do.

01:29:07.968 --> 01:29:10.679
I'm‒

01:29:10.763 --> 01:29:12.765
One of them?

01:29:23.025 --> 01:29:27.946
This is what they
want for all of us.

01:29:47.966 --> 01:29:49.968
<i>[Logan]
It's over, Jean.</i>

01:29:52.513 --> 01:29:54.473
It's over.

01:29:55.641 --> 01:29:57.601
[ Shouting ]

01:29:57.684 --> 01:29:59.645
No! Don't shoot!

01:30:13.200 --> 01:30:15.536
No!

01:30:16.870 --> 01:30:19.164
No‒

01:30:31.593 --> 01:30:34.680
- Everybody, get out of here!
- [ Clamoring ]

01:30:43.188 --> 01:30:45.190
<i>[Kitty]
Bobby!</i>

01:30:55.451 --> 01:30:57.453
What have I done?

01:31:08.213 --> 01:31:10.132
I'm the only one
who can stop her.

01:31:10.215 --> 01:31:13.218
Get everyone
to safety. Go!

01:31:17.973 --> 01:31:20.434
Jean!

01:32:05.896 --> 01:32:09.399
Jean, I know
you're still there!

01:32:56.321 --> 01:32:58.532
You would die for them?

01:33:00.701 --> 01:33:02.661
No. Not for them.

01:33:03.996 --> 01:33:06.164
For you.
[ Gasps]

01:33:07.833 --> 01:33:09.835
For you.

01:33:14.881 --> 01:33:16.883
Save me.

01:33:18.218 --> 01:33:20.178
I love you.

01:33:53.086 --> 01:33:56.006
No!

01:34:59.403 --> 01:35:01.405
You're back.

01:35:08.829 --> 01:35:11.331
I'm sorry.

01:35:11.415 --> 01:35:13.375
I had to.

01:35:13.458 --> 01:35:15.877
This isn't
what I wanted.

01:35:15.961 --> 01:35:17.921
I know.

01:35:18.004 --> 01:35:19.965
It's what I wanted.

01:35:29.516 --> 01:35:31.977
<i>[Boy]
Don't worry, Dad.
I'll call.</i>

01:35:33.145 --> 01:35:35.147
Hey.

01:35:35.230 --> 01:35:37.190
Good to
see you, buddy.

01:35:37.274 --> 01:35:40.944
<i>[President]
